&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;Scripture&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We heard him say, I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and within three days I will build another made without hands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ScriptureRef2&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mark 15: 42-45&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;Scripture&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;sup&gt;42&lt;/sup&gt; And now when the even was come, because it was the preparation, that is, &lt;strong&gt; the day before the sabbath &lt;/strong&gt; ,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;sup&gt;43&lt;/sup&gt; Joseph of Arimathaea, an honourable counsellor, which also waited for the kingdom of God, came, and went in boldly unto Pilate, and craved the body of Jesus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;sup&gt;44&lt;/sup&gt; And Pilate marvelled if he were already dead: and calling unto him the centurion, he asked him whether he had been any while dead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;sup&gt;45&lt;/sup&gt; And when he knew it of the centurion, he gave the body to Joseph.&lt;/p&gt;
